A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Safety – Gun Buyback Programs – Destruction of Firearms
3 FOR the purpose of requiring a person or an entity operating a gun buyback program to
4 destroy a firearm, including all components and parts attached to the firearm, that
5 is traded in at a certain gun buyback program; authorizing a certain person or entity
6 to contract with a law enforcement agency, an organization, or a business to destroy
7 certain firearms; requiring the Secretary of State Police to revoke a certain person’s
8 dealer’s license if the person violates the provisions of this Act; and generally relating
9 to gun buyback programs.
