5 (A) (1) (I) SUBJECT TO SUBPARAGRAPH (II) OF THIS PARAGRAPH, A
6 PERSON OR AN ENTITY OPERATING A GUN BUYBACK PROGRAM SHALL DESTROY A
7 FIREARM, INCLUDING EVERY COMPONENT AND PART ATTACHED TO THE FIREARM,
8 THAT IS TRADED IN AT A GUN BUYBACK PROGRAM.
9 (II) THE DESTRUCTION REQUIRED UNDER SUBPARAGRAPH (I)
10 OF THIS PARAGRAPH SHALL MAKE THE FIREARM AND EVERY COMPONENT AND PART
11 ATTACHED TO THE FIREARM PERMANENTLY INOPERABLE AND UNREPAIRABLE.
12 (2) A PERSON OR AN ENTITY MAY CONTRACT WITH A LAW
13 ENFORCEMENT AGENCY, AN ORGANIZATION, OR A BUSINESS TO SATISFY THE
14 REQUIREMENT UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION.
15 (B) A PERSON OR AN ENTITY THAT VIOLATES THIS SECTION IS SUBJECT TO
16 A FINE NOT EXCEEDING $10,000 PER VIOLATION.
17 (C) IF A PERSON VIOLATES THIS SECTION AND THE PERSON HOLDS A
18 DEALER’S LICENSE UNDER § 5–106 OF THIS TITLE:
19 (1) THE PERSON SHALL BE SUBJECT TO THE PENALTY PROVIDED IN
20 SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION; AND
21 (2) THE SECRETARY SHALL REVOKE THE PERSON’S DEALER’S
22 LICENSE IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 5–114 OF THIS TITLE.
23 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
24 October 1, 2025.

